  <summary>4/9/1987--Introduced.
Amends title II (Foreign Missions Act) of the State Department Basic Authorities Act of 1956 to restrict the travel within the United States of the personnel of certain international organizations and the personnel of the foreign missions of specified foreign countries. Limits such travel to the municipal city limits of the city in which such organization or mission is located. Allows a special rule for such travel within the Washington, D.C., metropolitan area. Authorizes the Attorney General to waive such restrictions for U.S. security or foreign policy interests.</summary>
